the typed pointer is a pointer to a very limited subset of types. It packs type information in with the pointer so that destroying and copying can be done without prior knowledge of its set up.

enum eolKeychainTypes

the typed pointer is a pointer to a very limited subset of types. It packs type information in with the pointer so that destroying and copying can be done without prior knowledge of its set up.

Enumerator:
eolKeychainVoid 

custom data

eolKeychainInt 
eolKeychainUint 
eolKeychainFloat 
eolKeychainString 

GString

eolKeychainList 

GList of something

eolKeychainHash 

GHashTable of something

eolKeychainCustom0 

for user defined types. EOL will not use Custom0 or after.
